# Windsurf Rules — HESEM MOM ERP

## MANDATORY WORKFLOW — Every Session
Read `.ai/AI-WORKFLOW.md` before starting. 4 phases:
1. ORIENT: `.ai/CONVENTIONS.md` + `.ai/repo-map.json` + `AGENTS.md`
2. LOCATE: Grep index files, never scan directories blindly
3. PLAN: state domain, tables, exact paths before any file creation
4. VERIFY: PHPStan + PHPUnit after every change

NEVER place files at repo root. NEVER put reports or dev notes inside `mom/docs/`.

## Context Loading — Always do this first
1. `.ai/repo-map.json` — project topology
2. `.ai/db-map/index.json` — Grep for table → get domain → read `.ai/db-map/<domain>.json`
3. `.ai/symbols.json` — Grep for class/method → get file path
4. `.ai/module-summaries/<domain>.md` — business rules for that domain
See `CLAUDE.md` for full protocol.

## Tech Stack
PHP 8.2+, PostgreSQL 16, Redis 7, RabbitMQ — custom MVC, no framework.
54 controllers, 122 services, 137 migrations, 766 tables.

## Non-negotiable Rules
- `declare(strict_types=1)` + `final class` on all PHP files
- Never rewrite to Laravel, Symfony, or any framework
- Every infra call (Redis, RabbitMQ, S3, Loki) needs a file-based fallback
- AI routes must return advisory proposals only — never mutate execution truth
- Validate at system boundaries only (user input, external APIs)

## File placement quick reference
| Type | Location |
|------|----------|
| AI prompts | `mom/docs/ai-prompts/` |
| Specs/architecture | `docs/architecture/` or `docs/backend/` |
